The Swiss-Swedish industrial group Asea Brown  Boveri (ABB) increased pre-tax consolidated profits by 32 percent to 246  million dollars in the first quarter from 187 million dollars in the same  period of last year, the company said on Wednesday.
But sales fell by 1.4 percent to 6.116 billion dollars from 6.205 billion  dollars in the first quarter of last year.
The value of orders received rose by eight percent to 8.189 billion  dollars, and in terms of local currencies, by 13 percent.
